title: 820-00840 - PPBUS_G3H high voltage 13.4V
message: [LEFT]hey guys, I have a 820-00840 (which im using 820-00875 board schematics and boardview), board had minor liquid spill around u7650, replaced u7650 and damaged capacitors (c7680, c7660, c7653, c7650), and also found PPBUS_G3H shorted to ground, after injecting power Q7680 was causing the short, replaced it, short is gone, but as of now PPBUS_G3H is high, at 13.4Vm any ideas what could be causing PPBUS to be high,[/LEFT]

title: 820-00840 - PPBUS_G3H high voltage 13.4V
message:
13V is correct voltage; your DMM can show more if has low battery.
Did you check it on F7000?
3V3_S5 present?
